WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.560
We’re making a profit!

00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:02.960
to close this place down?

00:00:03.480 --> 00:00:04.320
We can keep going!

00:00:04.320 --> 00:00:05.560
I barely did anything.

00:00:06.120 --> 00:00:07.360
It’s all thanks to your own effort, North.

00:00:08.080 --> 00:00:08.400
Hey!

00:00:08.400 --> 00:00:10.120
I can’t bring myself to trust a scammer.

00:00:10.600 --> 00:00:13.200
I’ll do whatever it takes
for you to trust me again.

00:00:13.520 --> 00:00:15.280
I want to resign from my role as the CEO.

00:00:15.600 --> 00:00:16.960
If you chose me and it didn’t work out,

00:00:17.600 --> 00:00:19.480
you’d lose everything you’ve built
with your family.

00:00:20.080 --> 00:00:21.800
I’d lose everything but still have you.

00:00:22.280 --> 00:00:23.440
I’ll always choose you.

00:00:23.880 --> 00:00:24.920
Then I choose you, too.

00:00:38.840 --> 00:00:41.440
I’ve never stared at the living room’s
ceiling like this before.

00:00:42.120 --> 00:00:43.720
I just noticed that the light bulb
is not working.

00:00:44.760 --> 00:00:46.400
Oh, you’re right.

00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:49.240
If we weren’t lying down here,
we wouldn’t have seen that.

00:00:50.320 --> 00:00:52.480
This is all the more reason to do it
on the couch more often.

00:00:53.360 --> 00:00:53.840
Baby.

00:00:55.760 --> 00:00:57.240
I mean, we have to keep an eye out
for this kind of thing, you know?

00:00:57.360 --> 00:00:59.160
Who knows which other
light bulbs are also broken?

00:00:59.400 --> 00:01:02.160
I wonder if the one on
the balcony is still working.

00:01:02.280 --> 00:01:02.720
Hey!

00:01:04.200 --> 00:01:04.960
Why are you blushing?

00:01:05.120 --> 00:01:06.480
We literally just did it.

00:01:07.080 --> 00:01:07.520
Tim.

00:01:08.280 --> 00:01:09.880
Fine. I’ll shut up.

00:01:12.440 --> 00:01:14.640
That almost didn’t sound like you.

00:01:15.640 --> 00:01:16.320
Do you like it?

00:01:18.280 --> 00:01:18.800
Of course.

00:01:19.120 --> 00:01:19.840
Very much.

00:01:30.440 --> 00:01:30.960
CHANHOM

00:01:30.960 --> 00:01:32.680
(Are you free today, Mek?)

00:01:40.800 --> 00:01:41.480
Was that work?

00:01:41.800 --> 00:01:44.280
Yes, something came up.

00:01:45.200 --> 00:01:47.920
I have some errands to run
but I’ll see you in the afternoon.

00:01:53.120 --> 00:01:53.400
NANA

00:01:53.400 --> 00:01:55.960
(The chauffeur is waiting for youdownstairs, sir.)

00:01:56.440 --> 00:01:56.920
I’m late.

00:01:57.560 --> 00:01:58.400
I have to go, baby.

00:02:08.440 --> 00:02:08.920
CHAMHOM

00:02:08.920 --> 00:02:10.360
(Well, darling?)

00:02:14.240 --> 00:02:15.400
BREAK UP WITH

00:02:16.520 --> 00:02:17.160
AIRY

00:02:17.160 --> 00:02:17.840
CHANHOM

00:02:17.840 --> 00:02:18.360
MON-ING

00:02:18.360 --> 00:02:18.960
FAHSAI

00:02:32.120 --> 00:02:33.560
I’m really sorry, Chanhom.

00:02:34.800 --> 00:02:35.400
But…

00:02:36.240 --> 00:02:39.480
I think we should call it quits.

00:02:40.200 --> 00:02:42.600
Let’s not see each other again.

00:02:43.520 --> 00:02:44.120
I knew it!

00:02:44.280 --> 00:02:47.360
I spent all that money on you and you
wouldn’t even go to a hotel with me!

00:02:58.240 --> 00:02:59.200
CHANHOM

00:02:59.600 --> 00:03:00.360
Oww…

00:03:01.200 --> 00:03:03.640
Chanhom, checked.

00:03:06.240 --> 00:03:08.200
My foot!

00:03:08.640 --> 00:03:10.800
That hurt.

00:03:26.680 --> 00:03:27.320
Ice, sir.

00:03:33.080 --> 00:03:33.920
Thanks, Max.

00:04:54.280 --> 00:04:55.240
AIRY

00:04:55.240 --> 00:04:56.960
(See you tomorrow.)

00:04:57.080 --> 00:05:00.720
(I’m excited to hear what
you need to talk to me about, Hong.)

00:05:16.160 --> 00:05:18.720
The interview for the wedding
will be tonight, Mr. Pai.

00:05:45.680 --> 00:05:48.520
Shall we take some photos?

00:05:49.400 --> 00:05:51.800
Please stand close, sirs.

00:05:52.120 --> 00:05:53.880
Right next to each other.

00:05:56.640 --> 00:05:59.200
Can you please look at each other?

00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:13.720
Why are you blushing?

00:06:14.320 --> 00:06:16.720
What happened to Mr. Confident
from this morning?

00:06:18.240 --> 00:06:18.920
No, it’s…

00:06:20.400 --> 00:06:21.480
You look nice today.

00:06:23.480 --> 00:06:24.040
I know.

00:06:30.400 --> 00:06:32.840
The next suits are for the party.

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:37.360
This is the twelfth suit.

00:06:37.600 --> 00:06:38.840
How many more
do we have to try on, Nana?

00:06:40.120 --> 00:06:43.080
There’s the suits for the tea ceremony,
for the press conference,

00:06:43.080 --> 00:06:44.280
and for the god worship ceremony.

00:06:49.200 --> 00:06:52.040
Can’t we… skip the god worship?

00:06:52.200 --> 00:06:53.040
No, we can’t!

00:06:53.280 --> 00:06:55.640
The Master said this is the
most auspicious time to pay respect

00:06:55.640 --> 00:06:57.400
and the opportunity doesn’t come by often.

00:06:57.600 --> 00:06:59.320
The ceremony will be quick and harmless.

00:06:59.480 --> 00:07:00.080
Please, sir.

00:07:00.280 --> 00:07:03.040
Ladies, will you please make way
so Mr. Pai can go and get changed?

00:07:03.240 --> 00:07:03.760
This way, sir.

00:07:03.760 --> 00:07:04.720
Please, get changed.

00:07:04.880 --> 00:07:05.200
Alright.

00:07:05.440 --> 00:07:06.560
You too, Mr. Tim.

00:07:21.680 --> 00:07:22.360
What do you want?

00:07:22.960 --> 00:07:23.480
(Hello.)

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:24.800
I need your advice.

00:07:25.360 --> 00:07:26.240
(Why are you whispering?)

00:07:27.120 --> 00:07:28.360
Why are you whispering?

00:07:30.560 --> 00:07:31.360
What do you need my advice for?

00:07:32.160 --> 00:07:35.000
I want North to trust me again.

00:07:35.760 --> 00:07:36.920
(You have any ideas on how to do that?)

00:07:37.560 --> 00:07:38.760
Aren’t you always so cocky?

00:07:39.120 --> 00:07:40.440
Just deal with it yourself.

00:07:40.520 --> 00:07:42.000
(I can barely save my own butt right now.)

00:07:42.400 --> 00:07:43.240
Come on.

00:07:43.680 --> 00:07:45.720
Alright, tell me what I can help you with.

00:07:46.000 --> 00:07:47.320
I’m good at giving advice, you know?

00:07:47.840 --> 00:07:48.440
It’s okay.

00:07:48.960 --> 00:07:50.240
Why don’t you save that advice for yourself?

00:07:50.640 --> 00:07:52.240
If you’re so smart, fix it on your own.

00:07:52.400 --> 00:07:53.880
Stop running to me for advice all the time.

00:07:54.120 --> 00:07:55.000
Tim, come on.

00:07:55.400 --> 00:07:56.280
It’s just this once.

00:07:56.600 --> 00:07:57.120
Please.

00:07:57.720 --> 00:08:00.040
Help this sinner turn himself around.

00:08:01.600 --> 00:08:04.640
What can I do to make North
trust me again?

00:08:05.320 --> 00:08:06.280
Please, Tim.

00:08:11.480 --> 00:08:12.520
You’re such a bother.

00:08:16.160 --> 00:08:18.120
(Off the top of my head,
I think you should…)

00:08:21.920 --> 00:08:24.920
WE ARE ALIVE AND WE REMAIN OPEN.

00:08:25.880 --> 00:08:26.720
This is cute.

00:08:28.880 --> 00:08:31.920
It’s so quiet on weekdays.

00:08:34.120 --> 00:08:35.200
It’s only normal.

00:08:35.760 --> 00:08:36.760
That’s business for ya.

00:08:37.360 --> 00:08:40.160
And it’s because U isn’t here
to attract customers as well.

00:08:44.200 --> 00:08:44.680
Oh.

00:08:45.200 --> 00:08:46.560
He’s not with you today?

00:08:48.120 --> 00:08:49.280
Are you out of your mind?

00:08:49.440 --> 00:08:50.760
Why would he be with me?

00:08:51.080 --> 00:08:53.200
That’s my… disputant.

00:08:53.600 --> 00:08:55.480
Oh, disputant, huh?

00:08:55.720 --> 00:08:58.280
I don’t see you making
any effort to sue him.

00:08:59.160 --> 00:09:00.800
I’m working on gathering evidence.

00:09:01.480 --> 00:09:02.080
Right.

00:09:04.440 --> 00:09:05.360
Let me just say…

00:09:05.880 --> 00:09:07.000
You won’t sue him.

00:09:07.600 --> 00:09:10.040
Not as long as you still like him.

00:09:10.200 --> 00:09:11.400
Hey, hey, hey.

00:09:11.800 --> 00:09:12.600
How’d you know that?

00:09:12.800 --> 00:09:13.960
You have a mirror at home, bud?

00:09:14.160 --> 00:09:15.280
Just go and look at the mirror,

00:09:15.360 --> 00:09:16.920
and you’ll see that it’s written
all over your face.

00:09:17.120 --> 00:09:18.840
Anyone, even from Mars, can… tell.

00:09:19.920 --> 00:09:21.960
Oh, there he is, the proof.

00:09:22.040 --> 00:09:22.920
No investigation needed.

00:09:27.520 --> 00:09:28.120
North.

00:09:28.400 --> 00:09:28.920
Oh, U.

00:09:29.520 --> 00:09:30.560
What are you doing here?

00:09:31.960 --> 00:09:33.440
I need you to come with me.

00:09:33.960 --> 00:09:34.960
I’m working.

00:09:35.480 --> 00:09:36.880
The place is packed, you know?

00:09:39.840 --> 00:09:41.440
It’s damn deserted, dude.

00:09:41.640 --> 00:09:42.600
You said so yourself.

00:09:44.520 --> 00:09:45.160
Come with me.

00:09:47.160 --> 00:09:48.800
No, I’m not going.

00:09:48.920 --> 00:09:50.360
And step aside.

00:09:50.680 --> 00:09:51.640
You’re blocking the entrance.

00:09:51.800 --> 00:09:56.520
If you don’t come with me, I’m telling Pai
you’re not closing the bakery down.

00:09:57.760 --> 00:09:58.240
Hey.

00:10:00.360 --> 00:10:01.320
You wouldn’t dare.

00:10:06.080 --> 00:10:07.360
Hey, North. North.

00:10:09.080 --> 00:10:09.600
U.

00:10:09.600 --> 00:10:10.040
Stop it.

00:10:10.360 --> 00:10:10.880
U!

00:10:10.880 --> 00:10:11.200
North.

00:10:11.200 --> 00:10:11.680
U.

00:10:12.160 --> 00:10:12.840
U!

00:10:13.160 --> 00:10:14.080
North, dude.

00:10:14.160 --> 00:10:14.640
U!

00:10:15.440 --> 00:10:16.400
U!

00:10:17.640 --> 00:10:18.760
Take it easy.

00:10:19.320 --> 00:10:19.800
Please.

00:10:20.040 --> 00:10:21.880
Let’s talk it out.

00:10:21.880 --> 00:10:22.640
What’s it gonna be?

00:10:22.920 --> 00:10:23.960
Please, U.

00:10:24.040 --> 00:10:25.720
Love thy neighbors.

00:10:25.720 --> 00:10:27.760
If you don’t come with me, we’re all dead.

00:10:27.760 --> 00:10:28.560
Take it easy.

00:10:28.640 --> 00:10:29.800
There’s always tomorrow.

00:10:32.160 --> 00:10:32.880
What?

00:10:33.160 --> 00:10:34.920
If you don’t love your neighbors,

00:10:35.400 --> 00:10:37.080
with whom will you sing the choir
when the judgement descends?

00:10:37.480 --> 00:10:38.320
That’s enough, you two.

00:10:39.240 --> 00:10:40.720
Just don’t say no and come with me.

00:10:43.440 --> 00:10:44.800
Yeah, North.

00:10:44.920 --> 00:10:45.600
You should go with him.

00:10:45.600 --> 00:10:46.320
That’s for the best.
Dude.

00:10:46.320 --> 00:10:47.280
Don’t be a problem.

00:10:48.840 --> 00:10:49.480
Fine.

00:10:50.880 --> 00:10:51.600
I’ll go with you.

00:10:54.560 --> 00:10:55.120
Good job.

00:10:56.960 --> 00:10:59.240
You didn’t need to make such a fuss.

00:11:00.920 --> 00:11:01.680
I can walk on my own.

00:11:09.240 --> 00:11:10.440
Again?

00:11:11.080 --> 00:11:12.600
You’d better not get me killed on the road.

00:11:14.680 --> 00:11:15.320
I won’t.

00:11:21.560 --> 00:11:22.120
Here.

00:11:31.600 --> 00:11:32.160
Come on.

00:11:32.560 --> 00:11:33.000
Alright.

00:11:41.080 --> 00:11:42.120
Hold on tight, kiddo.

00:11:51.800 --> 00:11:52.400
Let’s go.

00:12:16.960 --> 00:12:17.480
Let me help.

00:12:30.280 --> 00:12:33.080
Why did you take me here?

00:12:36.040 --> 00:12:37.800
Because I missed you.

00:12:43.320 --> 00:12:43.880
Mom?

00:12:59.800 --> 00:13:01.000
This is my place.

00:13:04.720 --> 00:13:06.360
This is everything I have.

00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:11.640
North, take a seat.

00:13:11.880 --> 00:13:13.320
Sit on the sofa.

00:13:23.080 --> 00:13:23.560
Hey.

00:13:24.040 --> 00:13:24.720
Don’t do this.

00:13:27.040 --> 00:13:29.520
If you sit on the floor, I sit on the floor.

00:13:42.200 --> 00:13:42.720
Oh.

00:13:43.200 --> 00:13:44.800
I wanted to see you today,

00:13:45.440 --> 00:13:49.240
because I need to tell you
what was real between us, and…

00:13:49.640 --> 00:13:51.760
what wasn’t.

00:13:56.720 --> 00:13:58.640
What isn’t true?

00:14:04.840 --> 00:14:08.800
(North doesn’t trust you now
because you lied to him.)

00:14:09.800 --> 00:14:11.880
Why don’t you come clean?

00:14:12.320 --> 00:14:14.400
Tell him what was real and what wasn’t.

00:14:14.960 --> 00:14:15.720
(Maybe that’ll help.)

00:14:21.640 --> 00:14:23.240
Do you remember the first day we met?

00:14:28.000 --> 00:14:30.880
You… saved me from falling into the water.

00:14:38.600 --> 00:14:38.960
Hey!

00:14:42.880 --> 00:14:43.240
You.

00:14:44.160 --> 00:14:46.120
I thought I was dying in those woods!

00:14:47.200 --> 00:14:49.640
If it wasn’t for you,
I wouldn’t have sprained my ankle!

00:14:49.840 --> 00:14:51.760
And we wouldn’t have to
stay the night in the forest!

00:14:52.120 --> 00:14:53.160
Hold on, North.

00:14:54.360 --> 00:14:57.680
It was my fault that you fell into the water.

00:14:58.320 --> 00:15:00.640
But getting lost in the woods
was not my plan.

00:15:00.640 --> 00:15:01.520
Yeah, whatever.

00:15:02.640 --> 00:15:03.320
What else?

00:15:07.320 --> 00:15:07.840
Actually…

00:15:08.880 --> 00:15:10.520
This is my place.

00:15:11.280 --> 00:15:14.400
The house we went to was a rental.

00:15:14.800 --> 00:15:15.480
I knew that.

00:15:16.200 --> 00:15:16.720
And…

00:15:18.320 --> 00:15:20.480
I am also part of the rental.

00:15:20.600 --> 00:15:21.720
I’m not his mother.

00:15:21.760 --> 00:15:22.440
What?

00:15:23.640 --> 00:15:24.880
Then, who are you, Auntie?

00:15:25.120 --> 00:15:26.880
This is Oom.

00:15:27.080 --> 00:15:27.840
I’m not his mom.

00:15:27.840 --> 00:15:28.360
Yep.

00:15:28.560 --> 00:15:29.320
I’m his aunt.

00:15:29.600 --> 00:15:30.080
Aunt.

00:15:32.000 --> 00:15:34.800
And that Auntie you met
at the house that day, North…

00:15:35.000 --> 00:15:35.680
That woman, yes.

00:15:35.680 --> 00:15:36.560
She’s not his aunt.

00:15:36.560 --> 00:15:37.040
She’s my mom.

00:15:37.640 --> 00:15:38.200
Her name is Nart.

00:15:39.520 --> 00:15:42.120
And this woman here is Oom.

00:15:43.040 --> 00:15:43.600
My aunt.

00:15:49.040 --> 00:15:49.760
Is that everything?

00:15:51.120 --> 00:15:52.680
Nothing more to confess, is there?

00:15:56.520 --> 00:15:59.440
Actually, there’s another person
who’s been helping me,

00:16:00.040 --> 00:16:00.520
and it’s

00:16:00.520 --> 00:16:01.000
U.

00:16:12.080 --> 00:16:12.640
Okay.

00:16:14.600 --> 00:16:15.040
I think…

00:16:16.600 --> 00:16:17.720
I’ve heard enough for today.

00:16:22.000 --> 00:16:22.480
North.

00:16:23.440 --> 00:16:24.280
Are you okay?

00:16:30.280 --> 00:16:34.600
I think… I really can’t trust anyone again.

00:16:48.840 --> 00:16:49.480
U.

00:16:51.120 --> 00:16:52.480
Go and wait outside.

00:16:53.360 --> 00:16:55.160
I need to talk to him.

00:16:56.960 --> 00:16:57.440
Go on.

00:16:59.280 --> 00:17:01.680
Come on! I won’t scam him!

00:17:01.680 --> 00:17:02.320
Go.

00:17:03.080 --> 00:17:03.720
Of course.

00:17:19.120 --> 00:17:19.920
North.

00:17:25.440 --> 00:17:28.360
Do you remember U’s mother?

00:17:28.880 --> 00:17:31.880
Nart, the woman you met
at the house in Sathorn?

00:17:35.600 --> 00:17:39.360
Nart is a con artist, just like us.

00:17:39.680 --> 00:17:44.360
But Nart is more callous than
any con artists I’ve met.

00:17:47.480 --> 00:17:48.160
How so?

00:17:52.320 --> 00:17:55.880
When Nart had U,
she raised him like a thief.

00:17:56.600 --> 00:17:57.840
She made a living as a thief.

00:17:57.960 --> 00:17:59.880
She taught him her trade all his life.

00:18:03.640 --> 00:18:06.520
And U just didn’t know
how to live any other way.

00:18:06.720 --> 00:18:07.240
U.

00:18:08.200 --> 00:18:09.680
For your education.

00:18:12.600 --> 00:18:14.000
Thank you, Ta.

00:18:18.480 --> 00:18:19.400
I have to go for now.

00:18:20.160 --> 00:18:21.800
Right. Of course.

00:18:28.640 --> 00:18:31.440
Ta doesn’t know what kind
of man you are, does she?

00:18:36.240 --> 00:18:39.600
If she found out you’re a con man,
it would break her heart.

00:18:43.040 --> 00:18:45.920
With his mother constantly betraying him,

00:18:47.000 --> 00:18:49.200
he just became wary of
everyone he meets.

00:18:59.240 --> 00:19:01.120
But he trusts you, North.

00:19:03.880 --> 00:19:04.560
Really?

00:19:09.880 --> 00:19:15.880
I want you to know how hard
U is trying to change.

00:19:17.160 --> 00:19:19.840
But whether you forgive him or not,

00:19:22.320 --> 00:19:23.960
that’s for you to decide.

00:19:36.880 --> 00:19:37.480
What you looking at?

00:19:41.040 --> 00:19:41.640
Nothing.

00:19:45.880 --> 00:19:46.600
Are you okay?

00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:48.880
I’m going home.

00:19:51.320 --> 00:19:52.840
Do you need a lift?

00:19:53.200 --> 00:19:54.760
No. I booked a ride.

00:19:55.360 --> 00:19:57.400
I don’t want to risk my life
on the open road.

00:21:34.760 --> 00:21:35.280
Pai.

00:21:37.600 --> 00:21:38.240
Let’s go.

00:21:45.240 --> 00:21:48.880
I was taking a break that night,
strolling in this garden.

00:21:49.400 --> 00:21:50.360
That’s when I met Tim.

00:21:50.880 --> 00:21:54.160
How did you feel
when you first met him, Mr. Pai?

00:21:55.560 --> 00:21:58.680
I thought he was… handsome.

00:21:59.160 --> 00:22:00.040
Something like that.

00:22:04.320 --> 00:22:08.200
He said he dropped his car key
into the water and lost it.

00:22:09.640 --> 00:22:14.240
As the owner of this mall,
I have to help my customers, don’t I?

00:22:15.400 --> 00:22:18.840
But as I was helping him,
I fell into the water myself.

00:22:19.640 --> 00:22:23.400
Tim probably didn’t want me to feel
embarrassed so he jumped in with me.

00:22:26.240 --> 00:22:26.880
Can I ask you something?

00:22:26.880 --> 00:22:27.280
Hmm?

00:22:27.720 --> 00:22:28.960
Did you like me right away?

00:22:31.440 --> 00:22:33.000
Not right away…

00:22:35.280 --> 00:22:36.480
But I did think you were interesting.

00:22:39.320 --> 00:22:40.000
What are you smiling at?

00:22:40.960 --> 00:22:41.480
Nothing.

00:22:42.080 --> 00:22:43.520
When did you fall for me?

00:22:44.840 --> 00:22:45.200
Me?

00:22:48.400 --> 00:22:49.840
If I have to be completely honest,

00:22:50.000 --> 00:22:51.200
as in, seriously honest…

00:22:52.840 --> 00:22:56.280
I liked Pai the moment I saw him.

00:22:56.440 --> 00:22:56.840
THREE MONTHS BEFORE PAI MET TIM

00:22:56.840 --> 00:23:00.680
How do you feel about this grand opening
for the perfume, Mr. Pai?

00:23:01.160 --> 00:23:06.400
First of all, I must say I am honored
to be here working with Richie Bloom.

00:23:06.400 --> 00:23:08.120
As you all know…

00:23:08.360 --> 00:23:11.640
I kind of knew Pai is the owner of the mall,

00:23:12.480 --> 00:23:17.800
I thought right away how different we were.

00:23:18.480 --> 00:23:19.520
I didn’t think we’d get along.

00:23:19.800 --> 00:23:21.360
I like quite a number of…

00:23:21.840 --> 00:23:23.520
But when I talked to him,

00:23:23.680 --> 00:23:24.600
and got to know him,

00:23:25.160 --> 00:23:27.120
I learned what kind of man Pai actually is.

00:23:27.800 --> 00:23:31.960
It just makes me love him
and care for him even more.

00:23:36.440 --> 00:23:40.680
It was already too late to back off
once I knew I fell for him.

00:23:46.600 --> 00:23:47.400
When I was young,

00:23:47.840 --> 00:23:52.320
I always saw how loving my parents were
and how happy they were.

00:23:53.880 --> 00:23:57.560
I never thought a life like that
was possible for me.

00:23:59.200 --> 00:24:00.280
But then I met Pai,

00:24:01.200 --> 00:24:04.440
and he made me realize that it could be
even better than I imagined.

00:24:15.720 --> 00:24:18.320
Can you all… look away for a second?

00:24:26.160 --> 00:24:26.600
What?

00:25:07.880 --> 00:25:08.560
U

00:25:56.480 --> 00:25:59.280
You didn’t have to come back if you were
gonna come back when we’re close.

00:26:04.560 --> 00:26:05.040
Well?

00:26:05.880 --> 00:26:07.240
Where did U take you?

00:26:07.360 --> 00:26:08.080
Spill it.

00:26:16.040 --> 00:26:16.720
What’s wrong now?

00:26:25.880 --> 00:26:29.800
Are you gonna tell me today or
should I wait for next week’s episode?

00:26:33.960 --> 00:26:34.640
Just spill the tea.

00:26:35.840 --> 00:26:36.560
Don’t be afraid.

00:26:37.360 --> 00:26:38.640
I’ll scream at you either way.

00:26:49.240 --> 00:26:52.040
I’ll admit that I like U.

00:26:55.200 --> 00:26:57.480
And I told him as much.

00:26:58.640 --> 00:27:00.040
I just can’t trust him again.

00:27:03.040 --> 00:27:06.840
So he came clean this afternoon.

00:27:08.960 --> 00:27:09.720
Came clean?

00:27:12.640 --> 00:27:14.480
About what lies he was telling me.

00:27:17.800 --> 00:27:19.160
But instead of hating him,

00:27:21.640 --> 00:27:24.480
and taking his confession to the police,

00:27:26.440 --> 00:27:27.120
I…

00:27:28.320 --> 00:27:32.200
I’m just sitting here confused and upset
that he came home late.

00:27:52.680 --> 00:27:53.120
North.

00:27:55.800 --> 00:27:58.120
I guessed you haven't had dinner.

00:27:58.360 --> 00:27:59.320
I bought you some rice porridge.

00:28:05.120 --> 00:28:07.400
You might not want
to see my face right now.

00:28:08.040 --> 00:28:09.920
You can take the dining table
and have dinner.

00:28:10.520 --> 00:28:11.760
I’ll wait downstairs in the lobby.

00:28:57.040 --> 00:29:01.120
I don’t even know
if the person I fell for even exists.

00:29:02.720 --> 00:29:05.680
But then, I also can’t leave him.

00:29:10.760 --> 00:29:11.600
Honestly, North,

00:29:12.480 --> 00:29:15.840
I wouldn’t know what to do either
if I were you.

00:29:26.320 --> 00:29:29.600
I put Mr. Kuea down for
your morning appointment today, sir.

00:29:29.600 --> 00:29:32.920
The rest of the appointments for Empire
will begin in the afternoon.

00:29:33.240 --> 00:29:34.200
Thank you, Nana.

00:29:35.040 --> 00:29:36.200
You can go back to the office.

00:29:37.280 --> 00:29:37.840
Pardon?

00:29:44.240 --> 00:29:45.280
Of course.

00:29:56.960 --> 00:29:58.080
Baby, what was that for?

00:29:58.360 --> 00:29:59.880
We’re going to see Kuea soon.

00:30:00.200 --> 00:30:01.360
I don’t want you acting up
out of jealousy again.

00:30:03.160 --> 00:30:04.120
That’s the reason?

00:30:04.640 --> 00:30:06.240
I’m not one to get jealous
so easily, you know?

00:30:06.240 --> 00:30:07.080
You can trust me.

00:30:08.400 --> 00:30:09.080
Are you sure?

00:30:09.320 --> 00:30:09.960
Of course.

00:30:12.800 --> 00:30:14.840
I did want kids at first.

00:30:15.240 --> 00:30:17.200
But whenever I think of Da Zhan’s face,

00:30:17.720 --> 00:30:18.960
I just have this urge to push him to the ground.

00:30:20.640 --> 00:30:21.560
That’s mean, Pai.

00:30:23.000 --> 00:30:24.240
Da Zhan is still just a kid, you know?

00:30:24.600 --> 00:30:25.680
But I don’t like him.

00:30:30.680 --> 00:30:31.200
Give it to me.

00:30:31.200 --> 00:30:31.760
I’ll do it.

00:30:46.160 --> 00:30:46.600
Tim.

00:30:47.200 --> 00:30:47.880
Come here.

00:30:59.600 --> 00:31:00.240
Where are we going?

00:31:06.240 --> 00:31:06.880
Get in there.

00:31:10.000 --> 00:31:10.680
Why?

00:31:13.240 --> 00:31:14.840
I’ll give you a cure for that jealousy.

00:31:16.640 --> 00:31:17.480
I wasn’t being jealous.

00:31:21.920 --> 00:31:22.680
It was my fault.

00:31:23.800 --> 00:31:25.840
I was caught up in talking to an old friend

00:31:26.680 --> 00:31:28.040
and ended up neglecting your feelings.

00:31:28.640 --> 00:31:29.480
You didn’t do anything, baby.

00:31:29.840 --> 00:31:31.960
It was Kuea who was bothering you.

00:31:32.360 --> 00:31:33.000
Baby.

00:31:33.400 --> 00:31:34.480
Kuea isn’t in love with me.

00:31:36.080 --> 00:31:37.560
How do you know that?

00:31:38.240 --> 00:31:39.760
He and I have been friends for ages.

00:31:39.760 --> 00:31:40.800
He isn’t in love with me.

00:31:41.040 --> 00:31:42.040
You don’t need to get jealous.

00:31:42.600 --> 00:31:45.520
Baby, I told you I’m not being jealous.

00:31:45.720 --> 00:31:47.240
I’m, like, so cool with it.

00:31:49.760 --> 00:31:50.920
I’ll give you a kiss
if you admit you’re jealous.

00:31:51.720 --> 00:31:54.440
I should have punched his teeth in.

00:31:54.520 --> 00:31:58.000
To be honest, I was holding back for you.

00:31:58.120 --> 00:31:59.320
He’d better not do it again.

00:31:59.720 --> 00:32:01.840
I was burning with jealousy, Pai.

00:32:02.240 --> 00:32:02.840
That Kuea jerk.

00:32:04.000 --> 00:32:04.760
Get in there.

00:32:06.000 --> 00:32:06.440
But I

00:32:06.440 --> 00:32:08.200
Do you want that kiss or not?

00:32:09.240 --> 00:32:10.320
You can do it here.

00:32:10.320 --> 00:32:11.880
What are we sneaking about for?

00:32:12.120 --> 00:32:13.040
We can’t do it here.

00:32:13.040 --> 00:32:13.920
My employees are around.

00:32:14.360 --> 00:32:16.640
But you kissed me right
in the middle of the crowded mall.

00:32:17.000 --> 00:32:18.160
Those people mean nothing to me,

00:32:18.280 --> 00:32:19.920
but it would be embarrassing
in front of my own employees.

00:32:22.480 --> 00:32:23.880
Make it a combo.

00:32:24.280 --> 00:32:27.480
Kiss me here, here, here, and here.

00:32:28.240 --> 00:32:29.080
Just get in there.

00:32:39.040 --> 00:32:41.200
This is the initial plan I came up with.

00:32:41.320 --> 00:32:44.360
I’m thinking of an English-styled house,

00:32:44.360 --> 00:32:47.440
with plenty of space and Tudor decor.

00:32:48.600 --> 00:32:51.320
You came up with all this by yourself?

00:32:51.840 --> 00:32:52.280
Yes.

00:32:53.760 --> 00:32:55.680
You’re even better than Pai told me.

00:33:01.080 --> 00:33:02.520
If there’s nothing more to sort out,

00:33:03.040 --> 00:33:04.800
let’s pause the project for a while.

00:33:05.280 --> 00:33:08.560
Tim and I will probably be busy with
preparing for the wedding next week.

00:33:09.120 --> 00:33:12.120
Let’s talk more about it after the wedding.

00:33:13.600 --> 00:33:14.040
Of course.

00:33:15.240 --> 00:33:15.920
Oh, I nearly forgot.

00:33:16.280 --> 00:33:17.480
Baby, can I have the invitation?

00:33:18.000 --> 00:33:18.520
Sure.

00:33:22.840 --> 00:33:23.360
Here.

00:33:23.720 --> 00:33:24.960
We just got them today.

00:33:25.320 --> 00:33:26.480
We’ll look forward to seeing you, Kuea.

00:33:27.200 --> 00:33:27.960
Save the date.

00:33:37.680 --> 00:33:38.520
I’ll try to be there.

00:33:39.840 --> 00:33:40.400
Thank you.

00:33:49.880 --> 00:33:51.640
(I’m on my way to Bangkok.)

00:33:51.760 --> 00:33:53.200
(See you tonight.)

00:34:16.560 --> 00:34:17.480
U.

00:34:18.000 --> 00:34:20.600
You need to stop waiting outside my
bedroom door first thing in the morning.

00:34:21.840 --> 00:34:22.480
I’m sorry.

00:34:25.240 --> 00:34:27.280
What do you want?

00:34:35.200 --> 00:34:35.720
Whoa.

00:34:37.840 --> 00:34:39.480
I’m giving you back the 250 million.

00:34:40.160 --> 00:34:43.000
Although, this is only 249 million.

00:34:44.760 --> 00:34:45.800
I’ll have to owe you the rest.

00:34:46.360 --> 00:34:49.360
Nart stole one million from me.

00:34:56.560 --> 00:34:58.840
So you’ve been disappearing lately
because of this?

00:34:59.560 --> 00:35:00.080
Yeah.

00:35:01.120 --> 00:35:04.480
I’m sorry it took me a while
to return the money.

00:35:05.400 --> 00:35:07.280
I don’t know how to write a check.

00:35:08.880 --> 00:35:11.720
So I’ve been withdrawing cash
so I can return it to you.

00:35:16.960 --> 00:35:21.680
Can you believe me now that
I don’t want anything from you?

00:35:24.520 --> 00:35:25.800
The money you returned

00:35:26.080 --> 00:35:28.920
is nothing compared to
the marital assets you would get.

00:35:32.200 --> 00:35:33.880
Don’t ever think I’m not smart.

00:35:36.640 --> 00:35:39.440
Do you really think of me that way?

00:35:39.440 --> 00:35:39.840
Yes.

00:35:40.360 --> 00:35:44.040
Because marrying me is
a guaranteed ticket to one billion.

00:35:45.000 --> 00:35:45.760
Everyone knows that.

00:35:53.080 --> 00:35:53.960
Well, then…

00:35:54.880 --> 00:35:56.200
There’s no other way.

00:36:00.800 --> 00:36:01.800
Can I have the car key?

00:36:06.000 --> 00:36:06.720
What for?

00:36:08.720 --> 00:36:09.240
U!

00:36:09.880 --> 00:36:10.400
Let’s go.

00:36:10.560 --> 00:36:11.320
Let’s go where?

00:36:11.320 --> 00:36:11.800
Where are we going?

00:36:11.800 --> 00:36:12.320
Just come.

00:36:12.320 --> 00:36:12.720
U.

00:36:12.720 --> 00:36:13.240
U.

00:36:13.240 --> 00:36:13.840
North, come on.

00:36:13.840 --> 00:36:14.320
Come with me.

00:36:14.320 --> 00:36:14.840
U!

00:36:16.760 --> 00:36:17.560
Where are we going?

00:36:21.960 --> 00:36:22.440
Mama.

00:36:25.520 --> 00:36:26.080
Get in the car.

00:36:33.160 --> 00:36:33.640
Pure.

00:36:35.480 --> 00:36:36.080
Get in the car.

00:36:36.760 --> 00:36:37.360
Where are we going?

00:36:37.800 --> 00:36:38.320
Just hop in.

00:36:40.760 --> 00:36:41.480
Alright.

00:36:44.880 --> 00:36:46.320
Everyone, get off.

00:36:47.720 --> 00:36:50.000
Where are you taking me?

00:36:51.560 --> 00:36:52.320
District office.

00:36:56.560 --> 00:36:57.320
We’re getting a divorce.

00:37:19.640 --> 00:37:20.400
I didn’t order that.

00:37:27.320 --> 00:37:28.520
Hmm.

00:37:32.120 --> 00:37:33.200
Hong.

00:37:33.520 --> 00:37:35.400
You look amazing today.

00:37:36.160 --> 00:37:38.480
And you look beautiful as always, Airy.

00:37:39.400 --> 00:37:40.600
You sweet talker.

00:37:43.280 --> 00:37:44.600
The usual, please.

00:37:45.080 --> 00:37:45.680
Yes, sir.

00:37:51.320 --> 00:37:51.920
Airy.

00:37:52.880 --> 00:37:57.040
There’s something
I need to ask of you today.

00:37:57.720 --> 00:37:58.560
Of course.

00:37:59.080 --> 00:38:00.520
How much do you want?

00:38:00.520 --> 00:38:01.200
Just tell me.

00:38:01.480 --> 00:38:03.560
Oh, it’s not that.

00:38:04.400 --> 00:38:05.040
It’s…

00:38:12.000 --> 00:38:12.560
Here.

00:38:16.080 --> 00:38:19.120
This is everything you gave me.

00:38:20.040 --> 00:38:21.960
I want to give them back to you.

00:38:22.520 --> 00:38:25.240
It’s everything I could find.

00:38:30.400 --> 00:38:35.000
Does breaking up with me scare you?

00:38:37.920 --> 00:38:38.440
Uh…

00:38:39.840 --> 00:38:40.600
Hong.

00:38:41.000 --> 00:38:46.320
I knew you’d find the right person
one day and want to stop doing this.

00:38:47.120 --> 00:38:49.520
I might be a tiny bit sad today,

00:38:50.200 --> 00:38:52.920
but I always knew
it was never going to be me.

00:39:00.160 --> 00:39:01.840
Congratulations, Hong.

00:39:02.480 --> 00:39:04.680
You should keep these gifts.

00:39:04.880 --> 00:39:06.320
I gave them to you because I wanted to.

00:39:06.880 --> 00:39:09.120
I’m sure you need them more than I do.

00:39:11.040 --> 00:39:14.000
But I really wanted to
return them to you, Airy.

00:39:15.960 --> 00:39:16.800
How about this?

00:39:17.560 --> 00:39:21.040
Give me one last hug
and we have ourselves a fair deal.

00:39:22.280 --> 00:39:22.680
Alright.

00:39:28.400 --> 00:39:29.120
AIRY

00:39:39.400 --> 00:39:40.320
Hello, Mama

00:39:40.320 --> 00:39:41.440
(Yes, love?)

00:39:42.480 --> 00:39:47.320
I’m calling to tell you
I have to postpone my visit.

00:39:48.240 --> 00:39:50.400
I got a new job.

00:39:51.760 --> 00:39:53.040
(That’s more than alright, love.)

00:39:53.040 --> 00:39:54.280
(You’re doing well, I hope?)

00:39:54.840 --> 00:39:55.360
Yes.

00:40:00.120 --> 00:40:00.720
Mama.

00:40:02.200 --> 00:40:03.320
I have a boyfriend.

00:40:04.320 --> 00:40:06.120
He’s really nice.

00:40:07.200 --> 00:40:08.280
I’m sure you’ll love him.

00:40:12.480 --> 00:40:13.040
Yes.

00:40:13.200 --> 00:40:14.160
See you.

00:40:24.440 --> 00:40:25.720
Do you have witnesses with you today?

00:40:27.640 --> 00:40:28.240
Yes.

00:40:30.000 --> 00:40:30.360
There.

00:40:35.480 --> 00:40:36.800
Please sign here.

00:40:43.200 --> 00:40:46.080
I didn’t agree to this divorce
because I gave up on you.

00:40:50.440 --> 00:40:53.600
But if getting divorced makes you trust me,

00:40:54.160 --> 00:40:55.000
I’ll gladly do it.

00:41:29.320 --> 00:41:30.520
DIVORCE CERTIFICATE

00:41:30.520 --> 00:41:33.520
ISSARA PREECHAJIT
NITIPON JEERAMONGKOLTHANUN

00:42:07.720 --> 00:42:08.360
Hold on…

00:42:09.320 --> 00:42:10.120
Who are you?

00:42:41.840 --> 00:42:42.720
I’ll return this, too.

00:42:56.400 --> 00:42:59.240
The day you gave me this plushie

00:43:00.120 --> 00:43:06.200
was the same day that my own mother
stole everything from me.

00:43:10.560 --> 00:43:16.240
It was also the first day
I realized I might be falling for you.

00:43:21.000 --> 00:43:21.880
I believed that

00:43:23.560 --> 00:43:27.320
somebody as nice as you
would never hurt me.

00:43:30.280 --> 00:43:31.400
What do you mean?

00:43:36.000 --> 00:43:37.200
in my entire life.

00:43:39.000 --> 00:43:40.680
I never trusted anyone

00:43:42.160 --> 00:43:45.760
I could never be sure if someone
I talked to or worked with

00:43:46.560 --> 00:43:53.280
would stab me in the back
or disappear from me.

00:43:57.320 --> 00:43:57.920
But…

00:44:01.320 --> 00:44:07.440
That day when I woke up next to you
was probably the only time in my life

00:44:08.760 --> 00:44:13.520
that I felt safe.

00:44:33.680 --> 00:44:34.560
So I…

00:44:36.360 --> 00:44:38.120
I want to wake up next to you every day.

00:44:39.000 --> 00:44:40.000
U!

00:44:40.000 --> 00:44:40.800
I know.

00:44:41.880 --> 00:44:44.200
Trust is hard to earn.

00:44:45.480 --> 00:44:48.440
I never trusted anyone myself.

00:44:49.240 --> 00:44:53.280
But you’re the one who changed my mind.

00:45:01.560 --> 00:45:02.400
I’ll go.

00:45:07.640 --> 00:45:08.240
Wait.

00:45:24.080 --> 00:45:26.040
You said you wouldn’t give up.

00:45:26.840 --> 00:45:29.600
If you gave up just because of this,

00:45:30.320 --> 00:45:32.240
how could I ever trust you again?

00:46:44.160 --> 00:46:45.440
MEMBERSHIP APPLICATION FOR ARCHITECT COUNCIL

00:46:45.440 --> 00:46:47.440
THANIN CHAIYANUWAT

00:47:17.920 --> 00:47:19.240
You don’t need that.

00:47:20.640 --> 00:47:21.400
I do.

00:47:21.400 --> 00:47:23.160
Our wedding is next week.

00:47:23.160 --> 00:47:24.120
I don’t want my skin to look dull.

00:47:26.160 --> 00:47:27.800
But I want to see you when you’re old.

00:47:28.320 --> 00:47:29.320
Old? No way.

00:47:30.840 --> 00:47:31.360
What?

00:47:31.720 --> 00:47:33.440
You don’t want to grow old with me?

00:47:34.200 --> 00:47:37.160
Just because we’ll grow old together
doesn’t mean I have to look old.

00:47:37.160 --> 00:47:37.800
Give me that.

00:47:38.200 --> 00:47:38.760
Nope.

00:47:39.160 --> 00:47:39.520
No way.

00:47:39.520 --> 00:47:40.160
Stop teasing me.

00:47:40.160 --> 00:47:40.600
Give me that.

00:47:41.400 --> 00:47:41.760
No way.

00:47:41.760 --> 00:47:42.360
Give it to me.

00:47:43.000 --> 00:47:43.600
I won’t.

00:47:43.600 --> 00:47:44.080
Give it back.

00:47:44.080 --> 00:47:45.080
Stay still.

00:47:45.480 --> 00:47:46.360
Give it back to me.

00:47:51.680 --> 00:47:52.520
You’re being so stubborn.

00:47:52.520 --> 00:47:53.360
Give it to me.

00:47:56.960 --> 00:47:57.760
You want this?

00:48:11.040 --> 00:48:11.640
Shall we?

00:48:12.640 --> 00:48:16.440
Please give a round of applause
to our newlyweds!

00:48:22.000 --> 00:48:22.960
What are you doing here, U?

00:48:24.000 --> 00:48:24.920
Mr. Pai.

00:48:26.200 --> 00:48:28.360
We’re here to tell you the truth.

00:48:31.640 --> 00:48:33.560
Another one gets kicked out
of the family, huh?

00:48:34.720 --> 00:48:35.680
I know you’re exhausted.

00:48:37.480 --> 00:48:38.720
Let me take care of you.